definitions.definition: An impression; the mark left behind by printing something.
definitions.example: The day left an imprint in my mind.

definitions.definition: The name and details of a publisher or printer, as printed in a book etc.; a publishing house.
A distinctive marking, symbol or logo.
definitions.example: The shirts bore the company imprint on the right sleeve.

definitions.definition: To leave a print, impression, image, etc.
definitions.example: For a fee, they can imprint the envelopes with a monogram.

definitions.definition: To learn something indelibly at a particular stage of life, such as who one's parents are.
To mark a gene as being from a particular parent so that only one of the two copies of the gene is expressed.
